Important Message for MHS Blackcat Athletics from MISD and MISD Athletics:

Due to a current Mexia Athlete being exposed to COVID-19 by a family member who tested positive, the 8am session of EDGE is suspended immediately until results of the student are provided to district administration. When results are received, parents and athletes will be contacted.

EDGE workouts that include Ladycats and MJH athletes will continue as normal. Thank you for your patience during this challenging time.

post_text:
Mexia Seniors and Parents,

Administration received requirements from the Governor's office yesterday and without any changes in our county's public health requirements, I am happy to announce that as of today, May 6, 2020, Mexia High School will be able to have their graduation on May 22 at Black Cat Field.

With the state's requirements our Class of 2020 High School Graduation will look very different than in previous years. More details will be coming soon from the High School as the Governor's requirements for social distancing are applied to our event.

Thank you for your patience as we work to make this graduation as memorable and safe as possible for all of our families.
text:
Mexia Seniors and Parents,

Administration received requirements from the Governor's office yesterday and without any changes in our county's public health requirements, I am happy to announce that as of today, May 6, 2020, Mexia High School will be able to have their graduation on May 22 at Black Cat Field.

With the state's requirements our Class of 2020 High School Graduation will look very different than in previous years. More details will be coming soon from the High School as the Governor's requirements for social distancing are applied to our event.

Thank you for your patience as we work to make this graduation as memorable and safe as possible for all of our families.

On the afternoon of Sunday, March 22, 2020, District Admin was notified that a sponsor on the MHS band trip tested positive for COVID-19. The sponsor does not live locally and returned to his home outside Limestone County immediately after the trip.
In abundance of caution the District has been in contact with with Texas Department of State Health, Region 7, which has advised that anyone who was on the trip showing symptoms of COVID-19 to call their doctor
As always during this public heath emergency please get the most current and accurate information at: https://www.dshs.texas.gov/coronavirus/

post_text: Mexia ISD is excited to welcome Triston Abron as the new Athletic Director and Head Football Coach for the Mexia Blackcats. Coach Abron joins Mexia from Paul Pewitt where his team was the 3A, Division II State Finalists. He was named Dave Campbell’s Texas Football Coach of the Year for 2019. Coach Abron brings a passion for excellence and we are excited about the future of Mexia ISD Athletics.

post_text: Mexia FFA has a rich tradition of succeeding at all levels. Over the past 4 years some of the notable awards are: Leadership Development Events has had 6 teams advance to area contest; Career Development Events has had 7 teams advance to the state contest; Mexia FFA students have participated at the state level in the talent and Spanish speaking creed contest. Also 14 students qualify for the Lonestar degree which is the highest award in the state. This is impressive because annually only about 1500 students receive this award.

post_text:
Hello Mexia Blackcat Families

Today, January 30th at approximately 1:10 p.m., the district received a threat against the high school. After preliminary investigations, the Mexia Police Department reinforced a soft (perimeter) lockdown with the assistance of the Texas Department of Public Safety.

Student safety continues to be our #1 priority. Tomorrow, Friday, January 31st, all schools will be open with increased presence from local and state law enforcement. We appreciate your patience and continued support.

Mexia ISD Administration

Mexia ISD Administration

As a safety precaution, Mexia HS was put on a brief soft lock down. All students are safe and the soft lock down has been lifted. Safety of our staff and students is our number one priority and we appreciate your support in this endeavor.
